\binom{4n}{2}-4\binom{n}{2}=\binom{4}{2}n^2.
2
\binom{4n}{2}
\{1,2,\ldots,4n\}.
2
\binom{4}{2}n^2
\{1,2,\ldots,4n\}
\big\{\{1,2,\ldots,n\},\{n+1,n+2,\ldots,2n\},\{2n+1,2n+2,\ldots,3n\},\{3n+1,3n+1,\ldots,4n\}\big\}.
2
4\binom{n}{2}
\{1,2,\ldots,4n\}
\big\{\{1,2,\ldots,n\},\{n+1,n+2,\ldots,2n\},\{2n+1,2n+2,\ldots,3n\},\{3n+1,3n+1,\ldots,4n\}\big\}.
\binom{4n}{2}=\binom{4}{2}n^2+4\binom{n}{2}.
